    <div class="AssessmentProblem.identifier">102783</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">RestrictedConstructedResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>Last month, there were 4 sunny days for every rainy day. If there were 30 days in the month, how many days were rainy? Explain your reasoning. If you get stuck, consider using a tape diagram.</p>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><p>There were 6 rainy days, because <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="45324">\(4+1=5\)</span>, so there are 5 units total. <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="45367">\(30\div5=6\)</span>, so each unit is worth 6.</p>
</div>
